cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on paraphrase generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel model based on the encoder-decoder framework, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The model uses word embeddings to capture the meaning of words, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the model's performance using metrics such as BLEU and ROUGE, which are commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval, respectively, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) possible categories as well.
